Privacy Policy for ERP Application

Effective Date: 25th Jan, 2024

Hare Krishna Movement Jaipur ("we," "us," or "our") operates the ERP Application (the "Web App"). This Privacy Policy outlines our practices regarding the collection, use, and sharing of personal information when users authenticate through Google for accessing the Web App.

Information We Collect:

Google Profile Information:
We may collect basic user profile details from your Google account, including but not limited to your name, email address, and profile picture.
How We Use Your Information:

Authentication:

We use the collected Google profile information for authentication purposes, allowing you to securely access and use the features of our ERP web application.
User Account Management:

Your Google profile information is used for managing and personalizing your user account within the ERP web application.
Communication:

We may use your email address for communication related to your account, such as important updates, notifications, and support.
Information Sharing:

Third-Party Services:
We do not share your Google profile information with any third-party services, except as required for the functionality of the ERP web application.
Your Choices:

Profile Information:
You can review and update the profile information associated with your Google account by visiting your Google account settings.
Security:

Data Security:
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information and prevent unauthorized access.
Cookies and Tracking:

Cookies:
We may use cookies to enhance your experience and for analytics purposes. You can adjust your browser settings to refuse cookies or indicate when a cookie is being sent.
Changes to This Privacy Policy:

Updates:
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting the revised policy.
Contact Us:

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at nrhdasa@gmail.com.
